  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b87\u0bb2\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0ba4\u0bbe\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bbe \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bae\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Monkey measles will hit Sri Lanka",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "Since 2019 till date, the Covid pandemic has thrown the entire world into a social and economic crisis and has also brought about political change.",
        "In Sri Lanka, the economic crisis has escalated into a political crisis, and the spread of the Covid pandemic has been the main factor behind the regime change.",
        "The World Health Organization (WHO) has declared measles as a 'public health emergency' as health precautions to protect against Covid-19 are being released.",
        "The World Health Organization (WHO) has classified monkeypox as a high-alert disease due to its rapid global spread.",
        "The Second Emergency Meeting of the World Health Organization on Infectious Diseases was held recently. Monkeypox has been declared a public health emergency based on various researches.",
        "Globally, more than 16,000 people have been affected by monkeypox in more than 75 countries and five people have died so far, the World Health Organization has announced.",
        "Monkeypox has been confirmed in Italy, Spain, Portugal, USA, Britain and India. Monkeypox is considered very common in remote areas of Central and West African countries. Monkeypox is a viral infection. Viral infection is very rare.",
        "Monkeypox infection is not easily spread from one person to another. There is no single vaccine for monkeypox. There are two types of monkeypox virus, the West African type and the Central African type.",
        "In the initial stage, the symptoms of monkeypox virus infection are fever, headache, swelling, back pain, muscle pain, body fatigue. When fever occurs, rashes occur on the body. These are mostly on the face. Small rashes usually occur on the palms and feet.",
        "Mumps has not yet been confirmed as a sexually transmitted disease, although preliminary studies suggest that it can be spread through close physical contact with one another during sex."
      ],
